==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*Of uncertain affinity;

===Pronunciation===
*θεός / theos / theh'-os

===Noun===
'''θεός'''

# a deity, especially (with G3588) the supreme Divinity; figuratively a magistrate; by Hebraism very: - X exceeding, [[God]], god [-ly, -ward].

===Inflection===
{{Template:grc-decl-2nd|θε}}
It is to be noted that Classical Greek contained no vocative singular, while later Greek allowed for both θεός and θεέ.

